The paper discusses the design of end-user programming environments and the annotation of software artifacts, which are topics related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The specific focus on the spreadsheet end-user programming paradigm suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The mention of literate programming also suggests a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
